        "soc_dashboard_update": {
            "title": "Eveus: update SOC cards and automations to use native entities",
            "description": "Eveus integration now creates the SOC input entities automatically for your Eveus charger device.\n\nThese new native entities replace the manually created `input_number.ev_*` helpers that were used before. The existing values are copied automatically, so you do not need to enter them again.\n\nPlease update all dashboard cards, automations, scripts, and templates that reference the old SOC helper entities.\n\nTo migrate, replace the old entity-ID prefix `input_number.ev_` with the new native Eveus prefix `number.eveus_ev_charger_`. One find-and-replace updates all four SOC inputs:\n\n- `input_number.ev_initial_soc` → `number.eveus_ev_charger_initial_soc`\n- `input_number.ev_target_soc` → `number.eveus_ev_charger_target_soc`\n- `input_number.ev_battery_capacity` → `number.eveus_ev_charger_battery_capacity`\n- `input_number.ev_soc_correction` → `number.eveus_ev_charger_soc_correction`\n\nYour existing `input_number.ev_*` helpers are left untouched. Eveus integration will not delete or modify any of them automatically.\n\nOnce you migrate all dashboards, automations, scripts, and templates to the new `number.eveus_ev_charger_*` entities, you can safely delete the old helpers if you no longer need them."
        },
        "ocpp_enabled": {
            "title": "Eveus OCPP is enabled — Home Assistant controls may not work",
            "description": "OCPP is turned on for your Eveus charger, so the charger is now controlled by the OCPP backend (for example, the Eveus mobile app).\n\nWhile OCPP is enabled, these Home Assistant controls may be overridden by the backend and may not take effect:\n- **Charging Current**\n- **Charge limits** (current, energy, time, money)\n- **Charging schedule**\n\n**To restore full Home Assistant control, turn OCPP off:**\n1. Open **Settings → Devices & Services → Eveus**.\n2. Select your charger device.\n3. Turn off the **Connect to OCPP** switch.\n\nThis warning clears automatically once OCPP is turned off — including when you disable it from the mobile app."
        }
    }
